1.00	The_Off_Hours	The Off Hours	The Off Hours is an American film written and directed by Seattle filmmaker Megan Griffiths. The full length feature film is akin to real life events that happened at a truck stop. It was distinguished due to its adoption of environmental and socially acceptable settings, which has won recognition by the Sustainable Style Foundation with a SSF Tag award. The film was premiered at the Sundance Film Festival in Park City, Utah on January 22, 2011.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/05/The_Off_Hours.jpg/220px-The_Off_Hours.jpg
